elements.title: Ennis House
elements.contents: ... that the Ennis House (pictured) was variously characterized as "a mausoleum, fortress, Tibetan monument, Mayan temple, and palace"?

elements.title: King Ohuede
elements.contents: ... that, in 12th-century Igodomigodo, King Ohuede proposed allowing women to inherit the throne in the absence of male heirs?

elements.title: skipped the cities of Nagoya and Kyoto
elements.contents: ... that one Japanese bullet train service once skipped the cities of Nagoya and Kyoto?

elements.title: Harris Schurmeier
elements.contents: ... that, when five consecutive Ranger spacecraft failed, Harris Schurmeier was put in charge with a mandate to transform the program?

elements.title: Here Will I Nest
elements.contents: ... that Here Will I Nest was the first dramatic Canadian feature film to be shot in colour, and the first film adaptation of a Canadian play?

elements.title: Prescott Currier
elements.contents: ... that Prescott Currier was one of the first Americans to visit the British code-breaking centre at Bletchley Park?

elements.title: memoir about her life with schizophrenia
elements.contents: ... that Elyn Saks's memoir about her life with schizophrenia won her a "Genius Grant"?

elements.title: Aristasia
elements.contents: ... that the subculture of Aristasia combined Guénonian Traditionalism with lesbian separatism?

elements.title: Bernardo de la Guardia
elements.contents: ... that fencer Bernardo de la Guardia was a competitor and a judge – at the same Olympic Games?
